# AutoDocJson - C# Documentation Generator

## Purpose

AutoDocJson is a C# port of the legacy PowerShell-based AutoDoc system. It parses legacy source code files (COBOL, REXX, BAT, PS1, SQL, C#) and generates interactive HTML documentation with Mermaid diagrams.

## Key Files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `ARCHITECTURE.md` | System architecture and component details |
| `POWERSHELL_ORIGINS.md` | Mapping of C# to original PowerShell sources |
| `AutoDocJson/Program.cs` | Main entry point |
| `AutoDocJson.Core/BatchRunner.cs` | Main orchestration logic |
| `AutoDocJson.Core/Logger.cs` | NLog-based logging |

## Running the Application

```bash
dotnet run --project AutoDocJson -- -Regenerate Clean -Parallel
```

### Command-Line Options

| Option | Values | Description |
|--------|--------|-------------|
| `-Regenerate` | None, All, Clean | Regeneration mode |
| `-OutputFolder` | Path | HTML output location |
| `-Parallel` | true/false | Enable parallel processing |
| `-ThreadPercentage` | 1-100 | CPU thread usage |
| `-MaxFilesPerType` | 0+ | Limit files (0=all) |

## Related PowerShell

The original PowerShell batch runner is at:
`C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\LegacyCodeTools\AutoDoc\AutoDocBatchRunner.ps1`

## Output Location

Generated HTML files are written to: `C:\opt\Webs\AutoDocJson\`

## MCP Server (autodoc-query)

AutoDocJson.Web hosts a Streamable HTTP MCP server at `/mcp` providing 3 tools:

| Tool | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `list_documents` | List all available doc files with metadata |
| `get_document` | Get full JSON content of a specific doc file |
| `search_documents` | Keyword search across all doc files |

The MCP endpoint is excluded from DedgeAuth via `SkipPathPrefixes` in `appsettings.json` -- no auth token required. Cursor registers it as `autodoc-query` (accessible as `user-autodoc-query`).

Setup: `pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\CodingTools\McpServers\Setup-AutoDocMcpCursor\Setup-AutoDocMcpCursor.ps1"`
